        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:55PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 655 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Idabel, or 33 miles north of Clarksville, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Idabel, Broken Bow, Wright City, Millerton, Garvin, Golden, Oak
Hill, Holly Creek, Glover and Farmers Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
